defaulta) defaultThe defaultdisproportionately defaulthighdefault risk to cyclists using the strategic road networkdefault.default Whereas rural major roads (not including motorways) carry a risk per mile travelled by car or motorcycle of four times higher than on minor urban roads; for cyclis
defaultts the risk is 28 times greater (Tabl
defaulte 1).
default&#xa0;
defaultMotorcyclists – who are in general at greater risk – are 5 times more likely to be killed than cyclists on minor urban roads, but are at a lower risk than cyclists when it comes to the major rural road network. Cycling on rural major roads is unacceptably 
defaultrisky – and correctly perceived as such by many. Yet many cycle trips must, in some way, either use, or cross, the major road network.
